The Telegraph - Calcutta : Business
 Tuesday, June 22, 2004  Business Briefs																								 New Delhi, June 21: Exports went up 29.43 per cent to touch the $5.8 billion-mark in May compared with $4.5 billion in the year-ago period. Iron ore registered a 188 per cent increase, while gems and jewellery grew 43 per cent. Commerce and industry minister Kamal Nath said there was a sharp increase in most of the sectors, including textiles and petroleum products, with only marine and leather recording a negative growth.																								 Singapore, June 21: Royal Dutch/Shell Group said its $400-million liquefied natural gas (LNG) terminal in India may receive its first shipment in December. The terminal, which is being built at Hazira in Gujarat, will have an initial capacity to import 5 million metric tonnes of LNG a year. 																								 Mumbai, June 21: The Reserve Bank of India has asked banks to refrain from claiming reimbursement of pension payment for government departments upfront and refund the excess amount erroneously claimed by them.																								 Mumbai, June 21: The Vadodara-based Alembic Ltd has concluded its internal restructuring by splitting operations into three strategic business units (SBUs) to prepare for competition in the post-patent regime in 2005. 																								 New Delhi, June 21: Videsh Sanchar Nigam (VSNL) has set up international headquarters in Singapore.
